  "response_text": "# Foods That Help Lower Cholesterol\n\n**Soluble fiber** (reduces LDL cholesterol)\n- Oats, barley, beans, lentils\n- Apples, berries, citrus fruits\n\n**Healthy fats** (improve cholesterol ratios)\n- Fatty fish (salmon, mackerel, sardines) - omega-3s\n- Olive oil, nuts, seeds\n- Avocados\n\n**Plant sterols/stanols** (block cholesterol absorption)\n- Fortified plant-based milks and yogurts\n- Some margarines\n\n**Other helpful foods**\n- Whole grains\n- Leafy greens\n- Legumes\n- Dark chocolate (in moderation)\n\n## General tips\n- Reduce **saturated fats** (fatty meats, full-fat dairy, coconut oil)\n- Limit **trans fats** (processed foods, fried items)\n- Include **regular physical activity**\n- Maintain a healthy weight\n\n**Note:** Diet helps, but genetics play a big role. If you have high cholesterol, talk with your doctor—lifestyle changes alone may not be enough, and medication might be needed.\n\nWhat aspect would you like to know more about?",
